    <header>
        <h1>Diet and Cycling</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <h2>Pre-Ride Nutrition</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Oats and berries for a balanced start</li>
            <li>Bananas for quick energy boost</li>
            <li>Hydrate with water or an electrolyte drink</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>During Ride Nutrition</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Energy gels or bars for sustained energy</li>
            <li>Keep sipping water or sports drink</li>
            <li>Fruits like oranges or grapes for a natural sugar boost</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Post-Ride Recovery</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Protein shake to repair muscles</li>
            <li>Carbs like whole grain bread or pasta to replenish energy</li>
            <li>Stay hydrated with water or a recovery drink</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cycling Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Warm up before you start cycling</li>
            <li>Maintain a steady pace</li>
            <li>Listen to your body and take breaks when needed</li>
        </ul>
    </main>
    <footer>
        <p>Ride safe and eat well!</p>
    </footer>
